1
00:01:43,737 --> 00:01:45,717
Step up. Please.

2
00:01:53,814 --> 00:01:55,816
Don't forget us in America.

3
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:07,264
Now we can finally find out
what this means.

4
00:02:19,272 --> 00:02:22,344
This is the story of my
brothers and sisters.

5
00:02:23,243 --> 00:02:26,281
When we were little,
we did not know many things.

6
00:02:26,446 --> 00:02:30,656
We did not know the world was big,
or that it was different from us.

7
00:02:30,817 --> 00:02:33,127
We only knew our villages in Sudan...

8
00:02:33,286 --> 00:02:36,665
which had been there
for thousands of years.

9
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:38,996
I should say Southern Sudan...

10
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:42,368
for we were soon to learn
that was an important distinction.

11
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:06,207
Papa? Papa! Papa!

12
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:46,713
Mama?

13
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:54,752
Our elders told us we would be safe
in Ethiopia, should anything happen.

14
00:07:54,908 --> 00:07:57,684
We had to walk towards the rising sun.

15
00:07:57,844 --> 00:08:02,315
We remembered their teaching
to survive the dangers of nature...

16
00:08:02,482 --> 00:08:05,463
but also to take
advantage of its offering.

17
00:11:28,721 --> 00:11:30,359
Kwol.
Mading.

18
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:32,730
Majok.
Agong.

19
00:16:24,851 --> 00:16:26,125
Theo!

20
00:18:12,892 --> 00:18:14,462
Gabriel!

21
00:19:51,791 --> 00:19:53,031
Theo!

22
00:19:54,994 --> 00:19:56,337
Theo!

23
00:21:58,617 --> 00:21:59,687
Shh.

24
00:23:52,464 --> 00:23:53,636
That's yours!

25
00:23:56,702 --> 00:23:58,079
Here you go!

26
00:24:20,592 --> 00:24:24,165
Um... There's no containers left
for you guys to put food in.

27
00:24:24,330 --> 00:24:26,310
So you guys will have to wait.

28
00:24:27,232 --> 00:24:28,905
Yeah. That will work.

29
00:24:57,763 --> 00:24:59,106
Hi.

30
00:25:00,666 --> 00:25:03,340
Hello. Can l...?

31
00:25:07,539 --> 00:25:11,510
We need to take him to the medical tent
so he can see a doctor.

32
00:25:12,711 --> 00:25:14,987
Uh, the medical tent?

33
00:25:52,251 --> 00:25:53,423
Amen.

34
00:26:16,875 --> 00:26:18,377
Breathe in.

35
00:26:19,912 --> 00:26:21,016
Breathe out.

36
00:26:22,214 --> 00:26:23,420
Excellent.

37
00:26:27,519 --> 00:26:29,624
She has a respiratory infection.

38
00:26:29,788 --> 00:26:32,359
Very good, Mamere. Moving on.

39
00:26:36,428 --> 00:26:38,203
Doctor Monyang?

40
00:26:38,964 --> 00:26:40,443
Be back.

41
00:26:41,467 --> 00:26:44,141
Yes?
I believe she has guinea worm.

42
00:26:46,972 --> 00:26:49,384
We're gonna make you feel better, okay?

43
00:26:53,612 --> 00:26:56,422
Someday when you become a doctor
and someone comes along...

44
00:26:56,582 --> 00:26:59,324
as smart as you,
don't be afraid to listen to them.

45
00:26:59,485 --> 00:27:00,759
I won't.

46
00:27:15,334 --> 00:27:18,178
Paul, where have you been?
Where is your shirt?

47
00:27:19,304 --> 00:27:20,942
I traded it to get these.

48
00:27:22,841 --> 00:27:24,115
Ifs called barter trade.

49
00:27:24,843 --> 00:27:26,117
Very good.

50
00:27:33,952 --> 00:27:35,329
The food is ready.

51
00:27:42,027 --> 00:27:44,007
Good?
It's very good.

52
00:27:44,530 --> 00:27:45,600
James.

53
00:27:58,143 --> 00:28:00,817
The promise of a better life in the camp...

54
00:28:00,979 --> 00:28:04,051
had long come and gone
since our arrival.

55
00:28:04,216 --> 00:28:08,221
Weeks became months,
and months became years.

56
00:28:08,620 --> 00:28:11,328
We found strength in sticking together.

57
00:28:11,490 --> 00:28:14,801
But our hope of ever leaving was fading.

58
00:28:19,364 --> 00:28:20,741
A new list is up.

59
00:28:24,403 --> 00:28:25,643
Come on, come on!

60
00:28:57,836 --> 00:28:58,940
Is there news?

61
00:29:01,073 --> 00:29:03,280
Yes, there is news.

62
00:29:05,711 --> 00:29:07,452
Our names are on that list!

63
00:29:07,913 --> 00:29:09,051
All of us?
Yes.

64
00:29:09,214 --> 00:29:11,091
We are going to Kansas City, Missouri!

65
00:29:16,521 --> 00:29:18,262
Are you sure?
I am sure.

66
00:29:18,457 --> 00:29:21,063
Really? We are going to America!

67
00:29:23,262 --> 00:29:27,802
Blessing be from God
who has to take us to this Kansas City!

68
00:29:32,904 --> 00:29:35,908
Not me. Not me.

69
00:29:41,713 --> 00:29:43,420
It's all right.

70
00:29:45,050 --> 00:29:46,552
It's all right.

71
00:30:05,904 --> 00:30:08,851
So this is what winter
in America feels like.

72
00:30:09,007 --> 00:30:12,318
This is frozen water. It's called ice.

73
00:30:12,477 --> 00:30:15,617
As all of you know,
there are four seasons in America.

74
00:30:15,981 --> 00:30:17,119
Yes, Jacob?

75
00:30:19,818 --> 00:30:21,161
Where are you going again?

76
00:30:21,953 --> 00:30:24,957
Ooh. Yes. You will have such cold.

77
00:30:25,123 --> 00:30:26,193
Mamere?

78
00:30:26,358 --> 00:30:30,329
What about education? I want to go
to college and then medical school.

79
00:30:30,495 --> 00:30:34,500
I know education is important to all of you,
and we're gonna talk about that tomorrow.

80
00:30:34,666 --> 00:30:37,146
But right now, we gotta focus on work.

81
00:30:37,636 --> 00:30:40,515
You're gonna have just a few months
to find a job.

82
00:30:40,672 --> 00:30:44,552
You're also gonna have to pay back
the government for your plane fare.

83
00:30:45,777 --> 00:30:48,280
Your date of birth is unknown?
Yes.

84
00:30:48,447 --> 00:30:51,951
Like a lot of the others,
you will be assigned January 1st.

85
00:30:53,051 --> 00:30:54,223
Why on this date?

86
00:30:54,386 --> 00:30:56,525
There will always be a party.

87
00:30:57,622 --> 00:30:59,624
Next.
Thank you.

88
00:31:43,735 --> 00:31:45,442
Relax.

89
00:31:52,210 --> 00:31:54,053
Goodbye, my brothers.

90
00:32:56,908 --> 00:33:01,288
Welcome to America!
We are so excited to have you with us.

91
00:33:01,446 --> 00:33:02,925
Did you have a good flight?

92
00:33:03,081 --> 00:33:04,287
It was okay.

93
00:33:04,449 --> 00:33:06,360
Uh-huh. And what are your names?

94
00:33:06,518 --> 00:33:07,929
My name is Mamere Deng.

95
00:33:08,119 --> 00:33:10,292
Okay. Mamere.
This is Paul.

96
00:33:10,455 --> 00:33:12,457
Paul.
Jeremiah.

97
00:33:12,624 --> 00:33:14,661
Jeremiah.
My sister, Abital.

98
00:33:14,860 --> 00:33:17,272
Abital. Okay.

99
00:33:17,963 --> 00:33:20,534
No... Abital Deng?

100
00:33:20,699 --> 00:33:23,680
Abital Deng.
I'm sorry. She's not on this list.

101
00:33:23,835 --> 00:33:25,508
Please, you must look again, please.

102
00:33:25,704 --> 00:33:27,047
No, see... Abital Deng!

103
00:33:27,706 --> 00:33:30,118
Abital Deng?
She's here!

104
00:33:31,009 --> 00:33:32,989
She's not on my list.
She's on mine.

105
00:33:33,144 --> 00:33:35,385
Yes, but she belongs
on the Kansas City list.

106
00:33:35,981 --> 00:33:41,055
Right, but not anymore. INS rules are that
females have to be placed with families.

107
00:33:41,219 --> 00:33:42,994
A family in Boston wants to take her.

108
00:33:43,154 --> 00:33:45,794
But this is her family.
You cannot take her from us.

109
00:33:45,957 --> 00:33:47,061
Those are the rules.

110
00:33:47,826 --> 00:33:49,897
I want to speak to another official.

111
00:33:50,795 --> 00:33:54,572
Why can't we put her up in a YWCA
for a few weeks while we find her a family?

112
00:33:56,167 --> 00:33:57,544
All right.

113
00:33:58,503 --> 00:34:00,744
I'm sorry. It's not gonna happen.

114
00:34:00,906 --> 00:34:02,681
Please, there must be something you can do.

115
00:34:02,841 --> 00:34:04,047
Guys, we have to go.

116
00:34:06,678 --> 00:34:09,090
I will find a way for us
to be together again.

117
00:34:09,648 --> 00:34:11,525
Okay.
Come.

118
00:34:15,186 --> 00:34:17,063
We'll be together again.

119
00:34:19,357 --> 00:34:23,237
All of you, promise to go to school
and work very hard.

120
00:34:27,432 --> 00:34:29,571
Be strong, my brother.

121
00:34:34,506 --> 00:34:35,678
Abital!

122
00:34:47,052 --> 00:34:49,089
How could you let that happen?

123
00:35:08,473 --> 00:35:09,952
Whoops. Heh-heh-heh.

124
00:35:13,044 --> 00:35:17,550
We are to look fora man named Mr. Pamela
Lowi from Faith Based Charities...

125
00:35:17,716 --> 00:35:21,095
at baggage claim. He will guide us.

126
00:35:35,266 --> 00:35:37,109
Yes? Hello, this is Carrie.

127
00:35:39,270 --> 00:35:40,840
Pick up who?

128
00:35:42,641 --> 00:35:44,985
I am sorry. That is not my problem.

129
00:35:45,910 --> 00:35:47,856
I'm not the Welcome Wagon.

130
00:35:48,013 --> 00:35:49,583
Can't they take a cab?

131
00:35:52,283 --> 00:35:54,320
Isn't there anybody else that can do this?

132
00:35:55,286 --> 00:35:56,697
Right now?

133
00:35:57,622 --> 00:36:00,296
All right. What airline?

134
00:36:01,693 --> 00:36:03,366
Okay, I'll be there.

135
00:36:04,462 --> 00:36:07,033
I gotta go.
God, I feel so cheap.

136
00:36:12,270 --> 00:36:14,181
Hey. I think you're forgetting something.

137
00:36:14,339 --> 00:36:16,945
They're from Africa.
I'm sure they're not gonna care.

138
00:36:18,476 --> 00:36:21,480
Next week?
Yeah. Next week.

139
00:36:51,710 --> 00:36:52,882
Hi!

140
00:36:53,478 --> 00:36:54,718
Hey.

141
00:36:55,146 --> 00:36:57,353
You must be the guys from, uh...

142
00:36:58,016 --> 00:36:59,427
Somalia?

143
00:37:00,385 --> 00:37:02,023
Senegal...?

144
00:37:02,187 --> 00:37:04,497
I'm sorry. I... Help me out here.
Sudan.

145
00:37:04,656 --> 00:37:07,034
Sudan! Yes, exactly.

146
00:37:07,525 --> 00:37:10,438
Hello.
My name is Mamere Deng.

147
00:37:10,662 --> 00:37:13,836
These are my brothers,
Jeremiah and Paul.

148
00:37:13,998 --> 00:37:17,172
You must be Pamela Lowi
from Faith Based Charities?

149
00:37:17,335 --> 00:37:20,873
No. I'm from the Forrester Employment
Agency. I'm gonna help you find jobs.

150
00:37:21,072 --> 00:37:23,177
I wasn't supposed to meet you
till tomorrow...

151
00:37:23,341 --> 00:37:25,617
but the gal who
from your resettlement agency...

152
00:37:25,777 --> 00:37:28,223
got stuck in a car... Anyway...

153
00:37:30,348 --> 00:37:32,555
Okay, uh...

154
00:37:33,351 --> 00:37:35,228
Did your luggage come down the chute?

155
00:37:37,455 --> 00:37:38,559
Great.

156
00:37:39,557 --> 00:37:41,036
Okay, let's go.

157
00:38:03,314 --> 00:38:04,622
Where is your village?

158
00:38:07,585 --> 00:38:09,496
My village?

159
00:38:10,388 --> 00:38:12,595
Uh, my village is...

160
00:38:12,757 --> 00:38:15,931
Elmwood Street close to the university,
I guess.

161
00:38:16,728 --> 00:38:21,074
May I ask you, let me say,
where is your darling?

162
00:38:21,232 --> 00:38:23,678
My darling?
Y0ur husband.

163
00:38:23,835 --> 00:38:25,837
Oh, no, no. I'm not married.

164
00:38:26,571 --> 00:38:30,178
If you do not have a husband, then it
is your children who provide for you?

165
00:38:30,341 --> 00:38:34,517
No. I don't have any children.
I'm not married.

166
00:38:34,679 --> 00:38:37,023
I provide for myself.

167
00:38:37,182 --> 00:38:39,458
Your survival skills are very impressive.

168
00:38:40,985 --> 00:38:42,020
Thanks.
Mm...

169
00:38:43,755 --> 00:38:46,463
My brothefs going to be sick.
Uh-oh. Oh, no.

170
00:38:55,934 --> 00:38:58,437
There's no way I can do that by Friday.

171
00:38:58,603 --> 00:39:01,345
No. I'm just not a miracle worker, Tom.

172
00:39:01,506 --> 00:39:03,952
I'll call him when I get
back in the office.

173
00:39:05,443 --> 00:39:07,286
She's talking alone.
I gotta go.

174
00:39:11,349 --> 00:39:14,057
He all right?
He has a weak stomach.

175
00:39:14,986 --> 00:39:17,990
Excuse me. What is that?

176
00:39:18,723 --> 00:39:19,793
Thafs McDonald's.

177
00:39:20,558 --> 00:39:22,128
It's a place to eat.

178
00:39:23,661 --> 00:39:26,005
When was the last time
you guys ate anything?

179
00:39:54,259 --> 00:39:56,899
Okay. Here it is.

180
00:39:57,328 --> 00:39:59,069
I'll call you tomorrow.

181
00:40:13,044 --> 00:40:14,955
Are you guys just gonna stand there?

182
00:40:34,065 --> 00:40:35,772
Hello?
Yeah!

183
00:40:37,068 --> 00:40:40,413
Hi.
Hello! Hello! You got here.

184
00:40:40,571 --> 00:40:42,949
Thank heavens. So sorry about the mix-up.

185
00:40:43,441 --> 00:40:48,288
Well, I'm Pamela Lowi, your volunteer with Faith
Based Charities, your resettlement agency.

186
00:40:49,080 --> 00:40:52,084
I'm gonna take it from here,
but thank you so, so much.

187
00:40:52,283 --> 00:40:55,059
No problem. I'll see you later.
All right.

188
00:40:55,320 --> 00:40:57,095
Excuse me?
Yeah.

189
00:40:57,255 --> 00:41:00,668
You make our hearts throb
for your many kind assists today.

190
00:41:01,426 --> 00:41:05,101
Would you be so kind to tell us your name?
Oh, sorry. Didn't I?

191
00:41:05,263 --> 00:41:06,469
My name's Carrie Davis.

192
00:41:07,065 --> 00:41:09,841
I'll call you tomorrow morning
and we'll start thejob hunt.

193
00:41:10,001 --> 00:41:13,505
May you find a husband
to fill your empty house.

194
00:41:16,107 --> 00:41:17,814
I'll work on that.

195
00:41:21,913 --> 00:41:24,416
We have a lot to cover.
This is your fridge.

196
00:41:24,615 --> 00:41:26,925
You got your cabinets up here,
your stove top.

197
00:41:27,085 --> 00:41:29,964
And I made you this.

198
00:41:33,758 --> 00:41:35,135
Okey-doke. Follow me.

199
00:41:35,860 --> 00:41:37,168
This is your bedroom.

200
00:41:37,362 --> 00:41:40,138
Cozy, huh? These bunk beds
were just donated to my church...

201
00:41:40,331 --> 00:41:42,834
so I snagged them for you.
They should do the trick.

202
00:41:43,001 --> 00:41:44,139
See this?

203
00:41:44,302 --> 00:41:46,543
If you flip it up, the light comes on.

204
00:41:47,805 --> 00:41:51,343
Isn't that great?
There's one of these in every room.

205
00:41:51,509 --> 00:41:56,015
Pamela, we have a sister,
and she has been separated from us.

206
00:41:56,180 --> 00:41:58,387
Yes, right, your sister.

207
00:41:58,549 --> 00:42:01,496
I'm so sorry. No family here wanted her.

208
00:42:01,652 --> 00:42:06,829
Switching the paperwork is near impossible,
but I'm sure she's with good people.

209
00:42:06,991 --> 00:42:08,629
Now, this is called a living room.

210
00:42:08,793 --> 00:42:13,139
And this light, you've gotta
turn on and off kind of thing.

211
00:42:13,297 --> 00:42:15,299
See?
What I meant to say was...

212
00:42:15,466 --> 00:42:18,470
she needs to be here with us.
Yes, we want her here.

213
00:42:18,870 --> 00:42:20,645
It wouldn't be proper.

214
00:42:20,805 --> 00:42:23,513
Besides, where would you put her
in this tiny place?

215
00:42:23,674 --> 00:42:26,678
Is there someone of authority
on these matters I can speak with?

216
00:42:26,878 --> 00:42:29,984
There's just no getting around it. Sorry.

217
00:42:31,082 --> 00:42:33,028
Let's go to the bathroom next.

218
00:42:33,184 --> 00:42:37,223
This is your only bathroom.
I did go ahead and get you some bathmatsm.

219
00:43:09,353 --> 00:43:11,560
It's very comfortable, no?

220
00:44:26,197 --> 00:44:27,642
It must be an alarm.

221
00:44:28,466 --> 00:44:29,467
Maybe.

222
00:44:49,020 --> 00:44:51,899
Mamere! Jeremiah! Open the door!

223
00:44:55,826 --> 00:44:57,134
You are here.

224
00:44:57,662 --> 00:45:00,404
Why didn't you answer the phone?
I've been calling you.

225
00:45:00,565 --> 00:45:04,911
For job hunt? We waited by the window,
but we did not hear your call.

226
00:45:05,069 --> 00:45:09,518
No, I called you on this.
This is a telephone.

227
00:45:09,674 --> 00:45:11,711
Do you know what a telephone is?

228
00:45:13,244 --> 00:45:15,349
Okay. We already missed
the 10:00 interview...

229
00:45:15,513 --> 00:45:17,493
let's head straight
to the restaurant.

230
00:45:31,929 --> 00:45:33,169
Carrie!

231
00:45:33,731 --> 00:45:36,575
Roger, hey. How are you?

232
00:45:36,734 --> 00:45:37,769
You never called me.

233
00:45:38,269 --> 00:45:40,408
I'm sorry. I've been so busy with work.

234
00:45:40,738 --> 00:45:44,880
Um... Guys, this is Roger.
He works with the local police force.

235
00:45:46,043 --> 00:45:49,513
We appreciate any person
who risks their life to uphold the law.

236
00:45:49,680 --> 00:45:52,183
May God bless you
and keep you safe from harm.

237
00:45:54,919 --> 00:45:57,900
I'll call you. Come on, guys!

238
00:45:58,055 --> 00:45:59,557
Nice to meet you.

239
00:46:03,794 --> 00:46:05,239
Hey.
Hey, Matt.

240
00:46:05,429 --> 00:46:08,137
What's up?
I know you have some openings in food prep...

241
00:46:08,299 --> 00:46:11,405
and it just so happens that these guys
have a lot of experience.

242
00:46:11,569 --> 00:46:13,378
Okay. I'll talk to them.

243
00:46:13,537 --> 00:46:14,743
Thank you.

244
00:46:14,905 --> 00:46:16,213
Hey.

245
00:46:16,374 --> 00:46:17,978
So...

246
00:46:18,643 --> 00:46:20,486
what brings you to the United States?

247
00:46:20,878 --> 00:46:26,089
My parents were killed in the civil war in
Sudan, and my sisters were taken as slaves.

248
00:46:29,920 --> 00:46:32,958
Do you have any restaurant experience?

249
00:46:33,658 --> 00:46:35,660
I would like to study to become a doctor.

250
00:46:37,795 --> 00:46:38,899
That's good.

251
00:46:39,964 --> 00:46:41,500
Are we going to eat now?

252
00:46:42,967 --> 00:46:43,968
Sure.

253
00:46:44,135 --> 00:46:46,137
You really want me to
hire these guys, Carrie?

254
00:46:46,304 --> 00:46:48,511
They have no experience.
They're too strange.

255
00:46:48,739 --> 00:46:51,151
If you can't take all of them,
just take one of them.

256
00:46:51,309 --> 00:46:54,085
We don't have any space right now.
