Thank you for your understanding.
Yeah, I'm gonna get right into it.

500
01:10:40,837 --> 01:10:44,114
Okay. I'll call you back. Bye.

501
01:10:49,011 --> 01:10:50,547
Mamere?

502
01:10:53,382 --> 01:10:54,759
Paul?

503
01:11:06,796 --> 01:11:08,400
Jeremiah?

504
01:11:45,835 --> 01:11:47,280
Hey.

505
01:11:52,308 --> 01:11:53,810
You did not call first.

506
01:11:54,010 --> 01:11:57,355
Ha-ha-ha. Busted. Welcome.

507
01:11:57,780 --> 01:11:59,987
What are you guys doing out here?
It's freezing.

508
01:12:00,149 --> 01:12:01,856
We miss seeing the stars.

509
01:12:05,521 --> 01:12:07,626
I'm looking for Paul. Have you seen him?

510
01:12:11,194 --> 01:12:13,538
May we invite you in for some tea?

511
01:12:15,765 --> 01:12:17,540
You know how to play dominoes?

512
01:12:17,700 --> 01:12:19,805
Uh, no.

513
01:12:21,204 --> 01:12:22,808
I teach you.

514
01:12:22,972 --> 01:12:24,610
(0K8)'-

515
01:12:25,842 --> 01:12:28,789
Paul comes home very late or not at all.

516
01:12:29,345 --> 01:12:31,382
Spends many days and nights
away from us.

517
01:12:31,547 --> 01:12:33,618
Doing what?

518
01:12:33,783 --> 01:12:35,387
I don't know.

519
01:12:36,152 --> 01:12:37,654
Did something happen?

520
01:12:38,387 --> 01:12:40,663
Lately Paul has not been Paul.

521
01:12:41,791 --> 01:12:45,398
He's your younger brother, right?
We do not share the same mother or father.

522
01:12:45,561 --> 01:12:49,737
Oh, I didn't know.
There is only me and my sister, Abital.

523
01:12:49,899 --> 01:12:52,140
Oh. Ls that the girl on the fridge?

524
01:12:52,802 --> 01:12:55,248
Yes.
Where is she?

525
01:12:55,404 --> 01:12:57,509
INS sent her to Boston.

526
01:12:58,207 --> 01:13:01,745
Because there is not one family
that wanted her here in Kansas City.

527
01:13:01,911 --> 01:13:03,356
Why?

528
01:13:04,580 --> 01:13:06,924
It's difficult for us to talk about.

529
01:13:09,151 --> 01:13:11,722
Because there was nothing I could do.

530
01:13:22,098 --> 01:13:24,203
Operator. How can Ihelp you?

531
01:13:24,400 --> 01:13:28,075
Hello, I need to speak
to Abital Deng right away.

532
01:13:28,237 --> 01:13:31,707
What city?
The city of Boston, please.

533
01:13:31,874 --> 01:13:33,785
Can you spell the name?

534
01:13:33,943 --> 01:13:37,550
D-E-N-G.

535
01:13:37,713 --> 01:13:39,351
You must find her, please.

536
01:13:39,548 --> 01:13:41,118
Calm down, sir. I need an address.

537
01:13:41,284 --> 01:13:46,427
Please! You must help me!
I need to speak to Abital Deng!

538
01:13:46,589 --> 01:13:47,897
Hello'?

539
01:13:59,936 --> 01:14:02,917
Hey! Hey! What do you think you're doing?

540
01:14:19,789 --> 01:14:21,166
What do you have to say?

541
01:14:21,324 --> 01:14:23,099
Nothing.
Nothing?

542
01:14:23,259 --> 01:14:25,933
You bring shame upon us
and you say nothing?

543
01:14:26,095 --> 01:14:29,838
You have been given a chance at life that
was taken from your brothers in Africa.

544
01:14:29,999 --> 01:14:32,605
And this is what you do with it?
How could you forget?

545
01:14:32,768 --> 01:14:37,513
No, it is you who forget. Who gave you
life, Mamere? Do you remember? I do.

546
01:14:37,740 --> 01:14:39,447
Do not tell me what I remember.

547
01:14:40,009 --> 01:14:42,250
I remember everything! Everything!

548
01:14:42,445 --> 01:14:45,983
You did not deserve to come here!
Your brothers died so you could leave!

549
01:14:46,148 --> 01:14:49,357
No, Theo died so you could leave.
Theo didn't want us to stop.

550
01:14:49,585 --> 01:14:52,998
He knew it was unsafe. But you made him.
You put us in danger.

551
01:14:57,126 --> 01:15:00,664
You should have stood up on that grass
that day, not Theo. I saw everything!

552
01:15:00,830 --> 01:15:03,208
Guys. You gotta...
This has nothing to do with you.

553
01:15:03,366 --> 01:15:06,006
This is not your war. I'm still your chief.

554
01:15:06,202 --> 01:15:08,876
You're not my chief. I know.
We all know. You killed Theo.

555
01:15:09,038 --> 01:15:11,712
You are not my chief!
You have never been my chief!

556
01:15:11,874 --> 01:15:13,785
Oh, my God! Get off of him!

557
01:15:13,976 --> 01:15:15,182
Carrie! Let them be!

558
01:15:15,344 --> 01:15:17,017
You guys, stop!
Let them be!

559
01:15:17,680 --> 01:15:18,988
Stop it!

560
01:15:20,516 --> 01:15:21,654
Get him off of him!

561
01:15:22,051 --> 01:15:23,997
Paul, come on!
Paul!

562
01:15:25,955 --> 01:15:28,799
You are not my chief!
You are not my chief!

563
01:15:29,358 --> 01:15:31,031
Mamere, are you okay?

564
01:15:39,969 --> 01:15:41,676
Don't look at me.

565
01:16:32,121 --> 01:16:33,429
Who's there?

566
01:16:33,923 --> 01:16:35,527
Hello'?

567
01:16:35,691 --> 01:16:37,568
My God, you're half frozen.

568
01:16:37,726 --> 01:16:39,728
I want to see my cows.

569
01:16:41,430 --> 01:16:42,738
I cannot make it stop, Jack.

570
01:16:42,932 --> 01:16:45,208
What can't you make stop?
I can't make it stop.

571
01:16:45,367 --> 01:16:46,402
Sit down.

572
01:16:52,741 --> 01:16:56,553
It's my fault. It's all my fault.

573
01:16:58,080 --> 01:16:59,491
What's your fault?

574
01:17:04,787 --> 01:17:09,736
I let my brother be taken away
by soldiers instead of me.

575
01:17:11,260 --> 01:17:13,934
They took him away thinking he was me.

576
01:17:14,830 --> 01:17:17,436
Theo told these soldiers he was all alone.

577
01:17:18,267 --> 01:17:21,976
To protect us. To protect me.

578
01:17:24,974 --> 01:17:28,922
It should have been me. I know this.
You don't know that, Mamere.

579
01:17:30,246 --> 01:17:31,589
Look at me.

580
01:17:34,150 --> 01:17:36,960
I was in the Army. I have been to war.

581
01:17:37,786 --> 01:17:40,198
But most of us were just average guys...

582
01:17:41,423 --> 01:17:43,630
being faced with unimaginable things...

583
01:17:43,826 --> 01:17:46,602
being asked to make choices
no one should have to make.

584
01:17:48,330 --> 01:17:53,336
Your brother made a choice
that night that was only his to make.

585
01:17:53,502 --> 01:17:54,640
It wasn't your choice.

586
01:17:54,803 --> 01:17:57,044
You didn't have that power.
You never did.

587
01:17:57,273 --> 01:18:01,016
L still hear the sounds of guns
and the crying of children.

588
01:18:04,346 --> 01:18:05,848
The cries...

589
01:18:08,384 --> 01:18:10,295
There were so many, Jack.

590
01:18:41,684 --> 01:18:45,757
I want you to be my brother, not my chief.

591
01:18:46,422 --> 01:18:48,026
No more.

592
01:19:29,298 --> 01:19:30,868
You don't have an appointment.

593
01:19:31,033 --> 01:19:35,778
Yeah. I know. I just stood in line
for two hours for you to tell me that?

594
01:19:35,938 --> 01:19:38,214
We have an opening in three months.

595
01:19:38,374 --> 01:19:40,877
Oh, no, I'm not leaving here
until I see a supervisor.

596
01:19:41,076 --> 01:19:44,455
If you'll step to the side and wait
until I help everyone in line here...

597
01:19:44,613 --> 01:19:47,287
I'm not stepping to the side
and I'm not waiting any more.

598
01:19:47,449 --> 01:19:51,829
Now, who do I have to screw around here
to see a goddamn immigration supervisor?

599
01:19:51,987 --> 01:19:54,263
Uh... Me.

600
01:19:54,723 --> 01:19:55,997
Great.

601
01:19:56,158 --> 01:19:57,603
Thanks, cupcake.

602
01:19:58,327 --> 01:20:02,002
Name?
Abital Deng. D-E-N-G.

603
01:20:03,999 --> 01:20:07,742
Age?
She's probably 21.

604
01:20:08,170 --> 01:20:11,014
Probably? Where is she from?

605
01:20:11,173 --> 01:20:12,481
Sudan.

606
01:20:13,942 --> 01:20:18,084
That's gonna be a problem.
Sudan has sponsored terrorist activity.

607
01:20:18,681 --> 01:20:21,685
We're not gonna be able to move her
across state lines so easily.

608
01:20:21,850 --> 01:20:24,797
We're talking about a kid here.
She's a child refugee of war.

609
01:20:24,987 --> 01:20:26,660
I know. It's absurd.

610
01:20:26,822 --> 01:20:30,964
But she's caught in a bureaucratic
crossfire, and it's gonna take a while.

611
01:20:31,160 --> 01:20:33,640
What can I do to make it move faster?

612
01:20:34,129 --> 01:20:36,336
You could hire a good immigration lawyer.

613
01:20:36,498 --> 01:20:39,342
But if you're telling me the reason
they were separated...

614
01:20:39,501 --> 01:20:45,110
is because there was no host family here for
her, then you're going to have to find one.

615
01:20:45,774 --> 01:20:48,186
Otherwise, there's no chance.

616
01:20:54,683 --> 01:20:55,889
H6Y-.Hey-

617
01:20:56,118 --> 01:20:58,997
Thanks for coming over on such short notice.
Yeah, sure.

618
01:20:59,154 --> 01:21:02,226
I know you're busy on Sundays
with church and everything...

619
01:21:02,391 --> 01:21:03,802
so thanks for coming.

620
01:21:03,959 --> 01:21:07,202
Uh-huh.
I need your help.

621
01:21:07,363 --> 01:21:09,365
Yeah. You do.

622
01:21:10,065 --> 01:21:13,171
I'm just wondering
what you think of this room.

623
01:21:13,335 --> 01:21:15,576
Whether I could turn it into a bedroom...

624
01:21:15,804 --> 01:21:19,183
maybe fix it up,
get rid of some of this stuff.

625
01:21:19,475 --> 01:21:21,716
I'm wondering if you think
it'd be good enough...

626
01:21:21,877 --> 01:21:24,050
for the INS to approve me
hosting a refugee?

627
01:21:24,213 --> 01:21:27,092
Or if your agency
would even back me up on that?

628
01:21:27,683 --> 01:21:31,062
If you can get the whole house presentable,
and not just this room, yeah.

629
01:21:31,220 --> 01:21:34,599
I think you can get approval.
What's wrong with the rest of the house?

630
01:21:34,823 --> 01:21:36,268
Really?

631
01:21:39,061 --> 01:21:41,098
All right. So where do we begin?

632
01:21:41,330 --> 01:21:43,003
Why don't you make us some coffee?

633
01:21:43,165 --> 01:21:46,169
I have tequila.
Praise the Lord.

634
01:21:46,335 --> 01:21:47,575
Great.

635
01:21:47,736 --> 01:21:50,239
Wow, this is amazing.
This looks really clean.

636
01:21:50,406 --> 01:21:51,908
We did it!

637
01:21:55,077 --> 01:21:56,420
Mm.

638
01:21:58,113 --> 01:22:00,184
So how many kids do you have anyway?

639
01:22:00,349 --> 01:22:02,727
Ugh. Too many.
Ha-ha-ha!

640
01:22:02,885 --> 01:22:06,526
Um... I don't know what I was thinking
to be honest.

641
01:22:12,461 --> 01:22:13,565
Hey.

642
01:22:14,730 --> 01:22:16,971
You sure you're ready to take this on?

643
01:22:18,867 --> 01:22:21,643
Yeah. Definitely.

644
01:22:28,043 --> 01:22:30,045
Okay, just one more.

645
01:22:56,738 --> 01:22:59,241
These Christmas decorations
are very elaborate, yes?

646
01:22:59,408 --> 01:23:01,115
I go all out for Christmas.

647
01:23:01,310 --> 01:23:04,018
I make my own baby Jesuses
out of papier-méché.

648
01:23:04,446 --> 01:23:06,949
But Santa Claus doesn't come to Sudan.

649
01:23:07,115 --> 01:23:09,595
Well, he's coming here.

650
01:23:09,751 --> 01:23:12,357
So, what time should we be expecting him?

651
01:23:12,588 --> 01:23:16,536
Ha-ha-ha.
Very late at night. And only if you're good.

652
01:23:16,692 --> 01:23:18,171
He sounds like a burglar to me.

653
01:23:20,629 --> 01:23:23,508
Mamere, I left some groceries on the porch.
Can you help me?

654
01:23:23,665 --> 01:23:25,201
Yes.
Thanks.

655
01:23:29,638 --> 01:23:31,049
Abital!

656
01:23:45,821 --> 01:23:47,494
I like this Christmas!

657
01:24:00,068 --> 01:24:01,376
You okay?

658
01:24:07,209 --> 01:24:08,813
You're doing really good!

659
01:24:29,565 --> 01:24:31,340
You look like an old bison!

660
01:24:56,258 --> 01:24:59,535
Happy birthday to you.

661
01:24:59,695 --> 01:25:03,734
Happy birthday, dear lost boys.

662
01:25:05,734 --> 01:25:10,877
My brothers. It is wonderful to see you all
here as we celebrate the day of our birth.

663
01:25:12,307 --> 01:25:17,154
We may not know the exact day we were born,
but we know about the day.

664
01:25:17,646 --> 01:25:19,489
Our mothers told us.

665
01:25:20,148 --> 01:25:23,322
Our mothers were very tall,
liked to tell us stories.

666
01:25:24,086 --> 01:25:28,432
We remember her words, even if we do not
remember the sound of her voice.

667
01:25:29,124 --> 01:25:32,162
She told us to remember who we are...

668
01:25:33,128 --> 01:25:35,301
and all who came before us.

669
01:25:35,464 --> 01:25:37,068
Thank you.

670
01:25:41,937 --> 01:25:43,416
Ab ital!

671
01:26:40,328 --> 01:26:42,330
Mm. This reminds me
of when I was a little girl.

672
01:26:42,497 --> 01:26:45,876
My sister and I used to sneak downstairs
when our parents were asleep...

673
01:26:46,034 --> 01:26:48,742
and we'd steal all the ice cream
and eat all of it.

674
01:26:49,304 --> 01:26:51,079
Is she like you, your sister?

675
01:26:51,239 --> 01:26:52,718
No.

676
01:26:52,874 --> 01:26:54,512
She was nice.

677
01:26:55,410 --> 01:26:58,983
My mom used to say that I was born
pissed off and Kelly was born chipper.

678
01:26:59,481 --> 01:27:00,824
"Chipper"?

679
01:27:00,982 --> 01:27:03,861
Happy. She was always happy.

680
01:27:04,586 --> 01:27:07,362
I used to tease her.
I used to call her Chipper.

681
01:27:07,756 --> 01:27:09,099
She hated it.

682
01:27:09,825 --> 01:27:11,395
Where is she?

683
01:27:11,560 --> 01:27:15,030
Oh, she got cancer two
years ago, and, uh...

684
01:27:17,065 --> 01:27:19,602
It just ripped through
her like a firestorm.

685
01:27:20,869 --> 01:27:24,043
And then, ahem, one day she was just gone.

686
01:27:26,875 --> 01:27:30,448
And you wonder why it was her
and not you?

687
01:28:01,076 --> 01:28:03,579
What?
My brother is doing laundry?

688
01:28:06,248 --> 01:28:08,489
You are good to marry. Ha-ha-ha!

689
01:28:12,754 --> 01:28:16,634
I got a letter from Kenya yesterday,
and I'm not sure what to believe.

690
01:28:18,260 --> 01:28:19,398
What?

691
01:28:19,961 --> 01:28:23,238
A man came into the camp a month
ago looking for us.

692
01:28:23,765 --> 01:28:26,974
It is possible he might have taken
our names off the list of people...

693
01:28:27,135 --> 01:28:30,582
who have immigrated in order
to pretend he's someone we know.

694
01:28:42,818 --> 01:28:44,695
It is not possible.

695
01:28:44,853 --> 01:28:46,423
But what if it is?

696
01:28:46,955 --> 01:28:49,993
What if ifs really him and he's alive?

697
01:28:54,963 --> 01:28:56,670
Theo.

698
01:29:07,275 --> 01:29:10,347
I don't understand. He's a refugee of war.
He needs asylum.

699
01:29:10,512 --> 01:29:14,619
All flights from the Kakuma Refugee Camp
have been stopped since 9/11.

700
01:29:14,783 --> 01:29:18,390
They have thousands there
waiting for the same opportunity.

701
01:29:18,553 --> 01:29:22,626
But he has his family here.
Faith Based Charities is ready to step in.

702
01:29:22,791 --> 01:29:25,829
I'll sponsor him. I'll pay for his ticket.
He can live with me.

703
01:29:25,994 --> 01:29:28,565
We could get him a work visa.
He knows cattle.

704
01:29:28,797 --> 01:29:33,007
You know, this might not even be
your brother, Mamere.

705
01:29:33,168 --> 01:29:37,344
There have been people who faked their identities
just to get out of situations like this.

706
01:29:37,505 --> 01:29:40,213
Which is why I need to go
and see for myself.

707
01:29:42,477 --> 01:29:44,479
Cat, could you give us a second, please?

708
01:29:44,646 --> 01:29:46,319
Thank you.

709
01:29:51,219 --> 01:29:52,892
You could try some embassy shopping.

710
01:29:53,054 --> 01:29:54,761
Explain that.
Okay.

711
01:29:54,923 --> 01:29:59,338
You go to Nairobi, you get into every
embassy you can and ask for asylum.

712
01:29:59,494 --> 01:30:02,941
You tell them your brothers story.
And you see if you can get a country...

713
01:30:03,098 --> 01:30:05,908
in good standing with the U.S.
to write him a visa. Okay?

714
01:30:06,067 --> 01:30:08,707
So he has to go halfway
around the world to do this?

715
01:30:08,870 --> 01:30:10,076
Yes.

716
01:30:10,238 --> 01:30:13,378
And it will all hinge on hitting
the right embassy on the right day.

717
01:30:14,509 --> 01:30:17,718
Providing that happens,
then we can work on transferring...

718
01:30:17,879 --> 01:30:20,621
the paperwork
through diplomatic channels.

719
01:30:56,151 --> 01:30:57,892
Plane food sucks.

720
01:30:58,286 --> 01:30:59,788
Thank you, Yardit.

721
01:31:03,091 --> 01:31:05,071
Call me if you need anything, okay?

722
01:32:10,558 --> 01:32:12,970
Excuse me. I am looking for my brother.

723
01:32:13,128 --> 01:32:15,802
He may have arrived here a month ago
from Northern Sudan.

724
01:32:15,997 --> 01:32:17,476
Where did you hear that?

725
01:32:17,665 --> 01:32:20,236
A letter to my sister
from somebody here in the camp.

726
01:32:20,402 --> 01:32:22,143
What is his name?

727
01:32:22,837 --> 01:32:24,373
Theo Deng.

728
01:32:25,874 --> 01:32:28,377
Deng. Yes.

729
01:32:30,011 --> 01:32:31,513
Thank you.

730
01:32:46,361 --> 01:32:49,240
I'm sorry. There is no one registered here
under that name.

731
01:32:49,397 --> 01:32:50,933
So what do I do?

732
01:32:51,099 --> 01:32:55,844
You can search the camp. Talk to everyone.
But be careful what you say.

733
01:32:56,004 --> 01:32:57,449
How many are here now?

734
01:32:57,605 --> 01:33:00,916
Almost one hundred thousand,
give or take a few.

735
01:33:01,076 --> 01:33:03,078
Okay. Thank you.
Hmm.

736
01:33:21,763 --> 01:33:25,404
Mamere? Mamere! Mamere Deng!

737
01:33:25,567 --> 01:33:26,602
James!

738
01:33:29,370 --> 01:33:31,782
Look at you! You are fat!
Heh-heh!

739
01:33:32,774 --> 01:33:35,050
How are you?
Oh. So-so.

740
01:33:35,877 --> 01:33:39,051
It is good you left here.
This is a darkness place.

741
01:33:39,981 --> 01:33:41,892
I'm so sorry.
It's okay.

742
01:33:42,484 --> 01:33:45,897
I am looking for my brother, Theo.
Have you seen him?

743
01:33:46,087 --> 01:33:48,795
What does he look like?
I am not sure. Maybe like me.

744
01:33:49,724 --> 01:33:52,728
Okay. I will let everyone know.
Come on. Come on.

745
01:35:31,426 --> 01:35:33,337
Mamere?
Theo!

746
01:35:37,865 --> 01:35:39,344
The others?

747
01:35:39,500 --> 01:35:44,245
Daniel is with God.
But the rest of us, we all made it.

748
01:35:44,405 --> 01:35:45,941
My God!

749
01:35:46,608 --> 01:35:47,951
My God!

750
01:36:07,195 --> 01:36:08,697
I hear something.

751
01:36:08,863 --> 01:36:11,969
Along time ago, I was very sick.

752
01:36:14,402 --> 01:36:17,940
Rheumatic fever. It has hurt your heart.

753
01:36:18,106 --> 01:36:20,882
No more. My heart is healed.

754
01:36:21,709 --> 01:36:23,382
Remove your shirt.

755
01:36:43,598 --> 01:36:45,168
Thank you.

756
01:36:50,171 --> 01:36:53,277
I am going to Nairobi
to get papers for you.

757
01:36:53,975 --> 01:36:55,682
It may take several days.

758
01:36:56,978 --> 01:36:59,959
Don't worry. I'll be back.

759
01:37:13,594 --> 01:37:14,834
Go.

760
01:37:14,996 --> 01:37:16,441
Next.

761
01:37:18,299 --> 01:37:20,176
I wish I could help you.

762
01:37:20,335 --> 01:37:23,282
Honestly, the world is a very confused
place right now.

763
01:37:23,438 --> 01:37:26,715
Indeed it is. No embassy would help me.

764
01:37:26,874 --> 01:37:29,218
I know. I'm sorry.

765
01:37:33,948 --> 01:37:35,393
Good luck.

766
01:37:43,024 --> 01:37:44,401
Hey, Theo.

767
01:37:48,329 --> 01:37:49,569
Is it done?

768
01:37:49,997 --> 01:37:52,068
Yes. It is done.

769
01:38:14,889 --> 01:38:16,232
James.

770
01:38:21,028 --> 01:38:22,939
Bye. Bye.

771
01:38:28,669 --> 01:38:30,376
Goodbye, my brothers!

772
01:38:32,407 --> 01:38:33,886
Goodbye, my brothers.

773
01:38:58,966 --> 01:39:00,411
Theo.

774
01:39:00,568 --> 01:39:04,311
When you get on the plane, a helpful
person will take you to your seal.

775
01:39:04,472 --> 01:39:06,042
You will show me these things.

776
01:39:10,478 --> 01:39:11,889
Theo.

777
01:39:12,647 --> 01:39:14,490
From this moment on...

778
01:39:15,716 --> 01:39:19,289
it is very important that you
only answer to the name Mamere.

779
01:39:19,487 --> 01:39:21,160
What are you saying?

780
01:39:23,057 --> 01:39:24,832
I could not get you any papers.

781
01:39:32,800 --> 01:39:35,303
No, Mamere. I cannot.
Yes, but you must.

782
01:39:35,470 --> 01:39:38,144
But it is a lie.
Yes, I know. But it is a good lie.

783
01:39:38,773 --> 01:39:43,279
But you...?
L will go to Kakuma. I can work at the hospital.

784
01:39:44,745 --> 01:39:46,452
Theo, you gave me life.

785
01:39:46,614 --> 01:39:50,084
That day in the elephant grass,
you gave us all life.

786
01:39:50,251 --> 01:39:52,128
I give it back to you.

787
01:39:52,954 --> 01:39:54,831
You are chief now.

788
01:40:04,532 --> 01:40:06,637
Now, go. Go. Go.

789
01:40:51,379 --> 01:40:53,916
Today we have a very special guest speaker.

790
01:40:54,081 --> 01:40:56,220
Many of you already know him.

791
01:40:56,384 --> 01:40:58,364
I'd like to welcome Jeremiah.

792
01:41:07,061 --> 01:41:10,270
This is the story of my
brothers and sisters.

793
01:41:10,431 --> 01:41:14,208
When we were children, our fathers
said, "Let something of me survive."

794
01:41:15,202 --> 01:41:17,182
We did not even know what does it mean.

795
01:41:17,939 --> 01:41:19,885
But then we saw our family murdered...

796
01:41:20,041 --> 01:41:23,511
and our villages destroyed,
and then we understood.

797
01:41:23,945 --> 01:41:28,587
We held inside ourselves the memories
of our forefathers and their teachings...

798
01:41:28,916 --> 01:41:31,123
so that we could move
fom/ard in the world.

799
01:41:31,719 --> 01:41:36,862
Like an invisible bridge their memory
connects our old life with our new.

800
01:41:41,362 --> 01:41:44,536
They say we were saved
by coming to the United States.

801
01:41:45,232 --> 01:41:47,644
But we also saved each other.

802
01:41:47,802 --> 01:41:50,282
And although our differences
may divide us...

803
01:41:50,438 --> 01:41:53,419
our common humanity unites us.

804
01:41:53,574 --> 01:41:57,920
For we are brothers and sisters, all of us.

805
01:41:58,079 --> 01:42:01,117
We try to share this wonderful world
we call home.

806
01:42:04,251 --> 01:42:06,458
They call us the Lost Boys of Sudan.

807
01:42:07,288 --> 01:42:09,165
I don't think we are lost.

808
01:42:09,924 --> 01:42:11,733
I think we are found.

